                        <h1 class="entry-title">Cookie Policy</h1>
                    </header><!-- .entry-header -->
        
                    <div class="entry-content">
                        <p><em>First of all, what are cookies</em></p>
<p>A cookie is a small text file (just a few bytes) exchanged between a website and your browser and typically used by the website manager to store information necessary to improve the navigation within the same website. Such data may constitute personal data in reference to Whereas clause no. 30 of EU Regulation 2016/679.</p>
<p>The <strong>Italy Family Hotels Consortium</strong> (based in Via Macanno 38/Q, 47923 Rimini, Italy, <a href="mailto:info@italyfamilyhotels.it">info@italyfamilyhotels.it</a>), as Data Controller of your personal data, manages cookies in compliance with Directive 2002/58/EC of the European Parliament and of the Council of 12 July 2002 concerning the processing of personal data and the protection of privacy in the electronic communications sector (Directive on privacy and electronic communications), for the following processing purposes.</p>
<p>To enable navigation of the website, the following types of cookies are present:<br />
&#8211; Technical cookies: functional and technical access to the website (no data is retained after the browser is closed);<br />
&#8211; Session cookies: used for navigation purposes or for managing custom content;<br />
&#8211; Analytics cookies: used for statistical and analysis purposes of the navigation and of the users.</p>
<p>Table of cookies</p>
