<p>These cookies may exchange information and track the user’s navigation, who is registered to one of these services. Information on how to disable such cookies is provided below; moreover, they can be disabled using the links provided.</p>
<p><strong>Data processing methods:</strong> your personal data may be processed electronically using software systems operated by third parties. Data processing for analytical statistical purposes is carried out in a temporary manner and in anonymous form. Any processing of data using third-party cookies is carried out as described in the specifications below.</p>
<p><strong>Recipients:</strong> for conducting certain activities, or to provide support to the functioning and organisation of activities, some data may be brought to the attention of others or communicated to recipients. These subjects are divided into the following groups:</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Third parties</span><br />
Communication to: natural or legal persons, public authority, service or any other body that is not the data subject, the data controller, the data processor and the persons authorised as data processors, including:<br />
&#8211; private entities or public service managers to whom it is necessary to disclose the data for the purposes identified above.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Data Processors</span><br />
The natural or legal person, public authority, service or other body which processes the personal data on behalf of the data controller:<br />
&#8211; Web agency: Hospitality Factory srl &#8211; based in Via Fieramosca, 1 47138 Riccione (RN), Italy;<br />
&#8211; Any other providers of IT services, web services, or other services necessary for the achievement of the purposes required to manage the relationship.</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Within the company structure</span><br />
Your data shall be processed only by personnel expressly authorised by the Data Controller, with the guarantee of the adoption of a relative confidentiality agreement and, in particular, by the following categories of employees:<br />
&#8211; Administration.</p>
<p><strong>Disclosure:</strong> Your personal data shall not in any way be disclosed.</p>
<p><strong>Managing cookies and disabling them</strong><br />
In case you have any doubts or concerns regarding the use of cookies, it is always possible to intervene to prevent that cookies are saved and/or read to and from your device, for example by changing the privacy settings within your browser in order to block certain types of cookies.</p>
<p>Since each browser (and often different versions of the same browser) can differ significantly from each other, if you prefer to act independently using your browser&#8217;s preferences, detailed information on the steps required is available in your browser’s help section. For an overview of the operation of cookies for the most common browsers, please visit <a href="https://cookiepedia.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.cookiepedia.co.uk</a>.<br />
If you wish, advertising companies allow you to forgo receiving targeted ads. This does not prevent cookies from being set, but blocks the use and collection of certain data by these companies. You can disable each individual cookie by following the links provided in the “Table of cookies”.<br />
For more information and the possibility to waive the use of certain types of cookies, visit <a href="http://www.youronlinechoices.eu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.youronlinechoices.eu</a></p>
 
